WEBVTT

00:16.400 --> 00:17.770
( <i>bell ringing )</i>

00:23.040 --> 00:24.770
( <i>whistle blowing )</i>

00:36.220 --> 00:40.820
( <i>playing the blues )</i>

01:27.400 --> 01:29.940
( <i>chattering )</i>

01:30.000 --> 01:33.240
NOW CLASS, I DON'T WANT
THIS FIELD TRIP TO BE A REPEAT

01:33.310 --> 01:36.740
OF OUR INFAMOUS VISIT
TO THE SPRINGFIELD STATE PRISON

01:36.810 --> 01:38.950
SO I WANT YOU ALL TO BE
ON YOUR BEST BEHAVIOR.

01:39.010 --> 01:40.820
ESPECIALLY YOU,
BART SIMPSON.

01:40.880 --> 01:43.620
MRS. KRABAPPEL,
I DIDN'T UNLOCK THAT DOOR.

01:47.550 --> 01:49.510
SORRY, LITTLE DUDES.

01:49.590 --> 01:51.990
PARTY HARDY
EQUALS TARDY.

01:52.060 --> 01:54.060
ALL RIGHT, CHILDREN,
COUNT OFF.

01:54.130 --> 01:55.160
ONE.
TWO.

01:55.230 --> 01:55.960
THREE.

01:56.030 --> 01:57.100
HEY, OTTO.

01:57.160 --> 01:58.290
HEY, OTTO, MAN.

01:58.360 --> 01:59.620
HEY, BART, DUDE!

01:59.700 --> 02:01.700
ANY NEW TATTOOS?

02:01.770 --> 02:02.900
FUNNY YOU SHOULD ASK, MAN.

02:02.970 --> 02:06.570
THIS MORNING I WOKE UP
WITH THIS ONE.

02:06.640 --> 02:07.610
COOL!

02:07.670 --> 02:08.930
I WANT ONE.

02:09.009 --> 02:11.580
NOT TILL YOU'RE 14,
MY LITTLE FRIEND.

02:14.780 --> 02:15.720
BART?

02:15.780 --> 02:17.390
BART SIMPSON?

02:17.450 --> 02:19.450
TAKE YOUR SEAT, BART.

02:20.590 --> 02:22.020
PLEASE, MRS. KRABAPPEL

02:22.090 --> 02:23.320
NOT NEXT TO WENDELL.

02:23.390 --> 02:25.090
HE PUKES ON EVERY BUS RIDE.

02:25.160 --> 02:26.160
NO OFFENSE, WENDELL.

02:26.230 --> 02:27.530
OH...

02:27.590 --> 02:29.590
BE THAT AS IT MAY,
IT'S THE ONLY SEAT LEFT.

02:29.660 --> 02:31.000
SO GET IN THERE!

02:31.060 --> 02:32.760
( <i>kids laughing )</i>

02:35.400 --> 02:38.640
PLEASE, TRY NOT TO SHAKE
THE SEAT LIKE THAT.

02:38.700 --> 02:40.060
Class, remember.

02:40.140 --> 02:42.480
DO NOT STICK ANY PART
OF YOUR BODY OUT THE WINDOW.

02:42.540 --> 02:44.750
WE ALL KNOW THE TRAGIC STORY
OF THE YOUNG MAN

02:44.810 --> 02:46.650
WHO STUCK HIS ARM
OUT THE WINDOW

02:46.710 --> 02:48.480
AND HAD IT RIPPED OFF
BY A BIG TRUCK COMING IN
THE OTHER DIRECTION.

02:48.550 --> 02:50.590
AND I WAS THAT BOY.

02:50.650 --> 02:51.820
( <i>laughter )</i>

02:51.880 --> 02:54.580
BART SIMPSON, SIT DOWN.

02:54.650 --> 02:56.310
I've had just about
enough of your
tomfoolery.

02:57.920 --> 02:59.120
OH...

02:59.190 --> 03:00.930
I DON'T FEEL SO HOT.

03:06.570 --> 03:07.440
( <i>yelling )</i>

03:21.750 --> 03:23.380
THERE'S OUR SCHOOL AGAIN.

03:23.450 --> 03:25.350
Mrs. Krabappel:
OTTO, ARE YOU SURE...

03:25.420 --> 03:27.290
IT'S A SHORTCUT,
MRS. K.

03:27.350 --> 03:28.650
TRUST ME.

03:30.390 --> 03:31.790
MRS. KRABAPPEL! MRS. KRABAPPEL!

03:31.860 --> 03:33.230
BART, NOT ANOTHER WORD
OUT OF YOU

03:33.290 --> 03:35.960
OR I'LL SUBJECT YOU
TO THE HUMILIATION

03:36.030 --> 03:37.970
OF MAKING YOU SING
IN FRONT OF THE CLASS.

03:38.030 --> 03:39.530
CAN I PICK THE SONG?

03:39.600 --> 03:43.400
NO. THE SONG WILL BE
"JOHN HENRY WAS A
STEEL-DRIVING MAN."

03:43.470 --> 03:44.810
OH, NO.

03:44.870 --> 03:48.410
WE'RE GOING TO MAKE
YOU SING, BART SIMPSON.

03:48.470 --> 03:50.670
YEAH, BART SIMPSON
WE'RE GOING TO
MAKE YOU SING.

03:50.740 --> 03:52.900
( <i>whispering and snickering )</i>

03:56.180 --> 03:58.020
WAAUUGGHH!

03:58.080 --> 03:59.640
THAT'S IT, BART!

03:59.720 --> 04:02.290
WHY CAN'T YOU
BE MORE LIKE, UH..?

04:02.350 --> 04:03.820
<i>US, MRS. KRABAPPEL?</i>

04:03.890 --> 04:06.190
YES. SHERRI AND TERRI.

04:06.260 --> 04:07.760
THEY KNOW
HOW TO BEHAVE.

04:09.500 --> 04:11.800
♪ DA DA DA DE-DA DA, WHOA! ♪

04:11.860 --> 04:14.290
♪ THEY TOOK BART SIMPSON
TO THE GRAVEYARD ♪

04:14.370 --> 04:16.240
♪ AND THEY BURIED HIM
IN THE SAND ♪

04:16.300 --> 04:17.209
♪ OH, YEAH! ♪

04:17.269 --> 04:18.540
♪ AND EVERY LOCOMOTIVE ♪

04:18.600 --> 04:19.959
♪ THAT COMES ROLLING BY ♪

04:20.040 --> 04:22.410
♪ SAID "THERE LIES
A STEEL-DRIVING MAN" ♪

04:22.470 --> 04:24.270
♪ LORD, LORD, OOH,
THERE LIES... ♪

04:24.340 --> 04:25.340
BART, ENOUGH!

04:25.410 --> 04:28.280
HEY, WENDELL,
YOU MADE IT, BUDDY.

04:28.350 --> 04:29.280
( <i>vomiting )</i>

04:29.350 --> 04:30.080
( <i>kids yelling )</i>

04:34.220 --> 04:37.130
AND SO THIS PLANT HARNESSES
THE POWER OF THE ATOM

04:37.190 --> 04:38.830
SO THAT WE HAVE ENERGY

04:38.890 --> 04:42.100
TO RUN EVERYTHING
FROM YOUR FAVORITE VIDEO GAME

04:42.160 --> 04:44.130
TO YUMMY COTTON CANDY MACHINES.

04:44.200 --> 04:45.730
( <i>applause )</i>

04:45.800 --> 04:48.170
LET'S LEARN MORE
ABOUT NUCLEAR ENERGY,
SHALL WE?

04:48.230 --> 04:49.390
LIGHTS.

04:49.470 --> 04:50.670
( <i>film projector running )</i>

04:55.110 --> 04:56.540
<i>WHEN MOST PEOPLE
THINK OF NUCLEAR ENERGY</i>

04:56.610 --> 04:59.080
<i>THEY THINK OF THIS...</i>

04:59.140 --> 05:00.410
( <i>yelling )</i>

05:00.480 --> 05:02.080
<i>...BUT WHEN WE TALK ABOUT
NUCLEAR ENERGY</i>

05:02.150 --> 05:06.250
<i>WE REALLY MEAN THIS.</i>

05:06.320 --> 05:08.460
<i>BUT WHAT EXACTLY
IS NUCLEAR ENERGY?</i>

05:08.520 --> 05:11.490
<i>I DON'T KNOW,
BUT I KNOW SOMEONE WHO DOES--</i>

05:11.560 --> 05:13.190
<i>SMILING JOE FISSION.</i>

05:13.260 --> 05:15.060
HI THERE, ENERGY EATERS.

05:15.130 --> 05:18.170
I'M SMILING JOE FISSION,
YOUR ATOMIC TOUR GUIDE

05:18.230 --> 05:20.800
TO THE STRANGE AND EXCITING
WORLD OF NUCLEAR POWER.

05:20.870 --> 05:23.600
AND THESE ARE
RODS OF URANIUM 235.

05:23.670 --> 05:24.910
HI, ROD.

05:24.970 --> 05:26.910
HEY, GOOD TO SEE YOU.

05:26.970 --> 05:28.240
YOU GUYS LOOK HOT.

05:28.310 --> 05:29.140
OF COURSE
WE'RE HOT.

05:29.210 --> 05:30.340
WE'RE RADIOACTIVE.

05:30.410 --> 05:32.650
HOW ABOUT A DIP IN THE POOL?

05:32.710 --> 05:34.780
LAST ONE IN'S
A ROTTEN ROD!

05:36.150 --> 05:39.090
THE RODS MAKE THE WATER SO HOT,
IT BOILS!

05:39.150 --> 05:41.690
OOCH! AH! OUCH! HEY!

05:41.750 --> 05:43.650
AND THE STEAM SPINS TURBINES

05:43.720 --> 05:45.390
THAT GENERATE ENERGY.

05:45.460 --> 05:48.130
Mrs. Krabappel:
BART, SIT DOWN!

05:48.190 --> 05:49.720
( <i>growling )</i>

05:49.800 --> 05:51.100
UH-OH. WHOOPS!

05:51.160 --> 05:52.960
LOOKS LIKE THERE'S A LITTLE
LEFTOVER NUCLEAR WASTE.

05:53.030 --> 05:54.140
NO PROBLEM.

05:54.200 --> 05:57.410
I'LL JUST PUT IT WHERE
NOBODY WILL FIND IT

05:57.470 --> 05:59.110
FOR A MILLION YEARS.

05:59.170 --> 06:02.140
NOW YOU KNOW THE WHOLE
TRUE STORY OF NUCLEAR ENERGY

06:02.210 --> 06:04.750
OUR NO-LONGER-MISUNDERSTOOD
FRIEND

06:04.810 --> 06:07.010
SO KEEP ON SMILING.

06:07.080 --> 06:08.120
( <i>kids cheering )</i>

06:10.250 --> 06:12.920
NOW LET'S HAVE EVEN MORE FUN.

06:23.130 --> 06:26.270
AND OVER HERE
IS OUR THERMAL REGULATOR.

06:26.330 --> 06:28.470
TO YOUR RIGHT IF YOU'LL LOOK
THROUGH THIS WINDOW

06:28.530 --> 06:32.200
YOU'LL SEE WHERE OUR WATER
REJOINS THE REST OF
NATURE'S BIOSPHERE.

06:35.840 --> 06:39.310
HEY BART, OUR DAD SAYS
YOUR DAD IS INCOMPETENT.

06:39.380 --> 06:40.780
WHAT DOES INCOMPETENT MEAN?

06:40.850 --> 06:43.720
IT MEANS HE SPENDS MORE TIME
YACKING AND SCARFING DOWN DONUTS

06:43.780 --> 06:45.620
THAN DOING HIS JOB.

06:45.680 --> 06:47.880
OH, OKAY.
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
PUTTING HIM DOWN.

06:49.190 --> 06:51.960
YOU KNOW, I DEFY ANYONE
TO TELL THE DIFFERENCE

06:52.020 --> 06:55.290
BETWEEN THESE DONUTS
AND ONES BAKED TODAY.

06:55.360 --> 06:58.430
HEY, MY BOY'S SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE ANY SECOND

06:58.500 --> 06:59.730
ON A FIELD TRIP.

06:59.800 --> 07:01.870
THEY BEEN THROUGH HERE YET?

07:01.930 --> 07:04.200
COME ON, SIMPSON.
IF THEY WANTED YOUR KID
TO SEE YOU

07:04.270 --> 07:06.670
SITTING AROUND ON YOUR BUTT
AND STUFFING YOUR FACE

07:06.740 --> 07:08.480
THEY'D TAKE HIM ON A TOUR
OF YOUR HOUSE.

07:08.540 --> 07:09.880
YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:09.940 --> 07:12.410
I GOT TO GET
WHERE THE ACTION IS.

07:12.480 --> 07:13.780
COMING THROUGH!

07:13.850 --> 07:15.750
HEY, THERE'S MY DAD.

07:15.810 --> 07:17.780
HEY, DAD!

07:17.850 --> 07:19.250
YO, HOMER!

07:19.320 --> 07:20.960
WOO, WOO! I'M UP HERE.

07:21.020 --> 07:22.090
OH, HI, BOY.

07:23.920 --> 07:26.050
( <i>sirens wailing )</i>

07:31.630 --> 07:33.000
ALL RIGHT,
WHO'S RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS?

07:34.430 --> 07:35.490
( <i>gulps )</i>

07:35.570 --> 07:37.210
I MIGHT HAVE KNOWN
IT WAS YOU, SIMPSON.

07:37.270 --> 07:38.040
BUT, SIR...

07:38.100 --> 07:39.730
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.

07:39.810 --> 07:40.940
YOU'RE FIRED.

07:41.010 --> 07:42.410
OH, HI, GIRLS.

07:42.470 --> 07:44.240
HI, DADDY.
HI, DADDY.

07:44.310 --> 07:45.410
OH...

07:57.460 --> 07:59.230
HERE'S A GOOD JOB

07:59.290 --> 08:00.660
AT THE FIREWORKS FACTORY.

08:00.730 --> 08:02.560
THOSE PERFECTIONISTS?
FORGET IT.

08:02.630 --> 08:03.800
Lisa: HOW ABOUT THIS?

08:03.860 --> 08:06.790
SUPERVISING TECHNICIAN
AT THE TOXIC WASTE DUMP.

08:06.870 --> 08:10.970
I'M NO SUPERVISING TECHNICIAN,
I'M A TECHNICAL SUPERVISOR.

08:11.040 --> 08:14.440
I'VE NEVER DONE ANYTHING
WORTHWHILE IN MY LIFE.

08:14.510 --> 08:16.440
I'M A BIG, WORTHLESS NOTHING.

08:16.510 --> 08:17.750
THERE, THERE, HOMER.

08:17.810 --> 08:19.110
YOU'LL FIND A JOB.

08:19.180 --> 08:21.420
YOU'VE CAUSED PLENTY
OF INDUSTRIAL ACCIDENTS

08:21.480 --> 08:23.350
AND YOU'VE ALWAYS BOUNCED BACK.

08:23.420 --> 08:24.290
YEAH, DAD.
YOU CAN DO IT.

08:24.350 --> 08:25.420
YEAH, GO FOR IT, DAD.

08:25.480 --> 08:26.440
YOU'RE RIGHT.

08:26.520 --> 08:27.420
I'M YOUNG

08:27.490 --> 08:28.360
I'M ABLE-BODIED

08:28.420 --> 08:29.490
AND I'LL TAKE ANYTHING.

08:29.550 --> 08:31.220
WATCH OUT, SPRINGFIELD.

08:31.290 --> 08:32.659
HERE I COME.

08:38.260 --> 08:40.690
DON'T GIVE UP, DAD.

08:40.770 --> 08:45.110
I'M JUST A TECHNICAL SUPERVISOR
WHO CARED TOO MUCH.

08:45.170 --> 08:46.040
( <i>ringing )</i>

08:46.100 --> 08:47.100
MOE'S TAVERN.

08:47.170 --> 08:49.080
Bart:
Is Mr. Freely there?

08:49.140 --> 08:50.080
WHO?

08:50.140 --> 08:52.710
Freely, first initial's I.P.

08:52.780 --> 08:53.920
HOLD ON, I'LL CHECK.

08:53.980 --> 08:56.980
UH, IS I.P. FREELY HERE?

08:57.050 --> 09:00.960
HEY, EVERYBODY, I.P. FREELY!

09:01.020 --> 09:02.890
( <i>laughing )</i>

09:02.950 --> 09:05.680
WAIT A MINUTE.

09:05.760 --> 09:08.100
LISTEN TO ME, YOU LOUSY BUM

09:08.160 --> 09:09.960
WHEN I GET A HOLD OF YOU,
YOU'RE DEAD.

09:10.030 --> 09:11.930
I SWEAR I'M GONNA
SLICE YOUR HEART IN HALF.

09:12.000 --> 09:16.740
( laughing )

09:16.800 --> 09:18.970
YOU'LL GET
THAT PUNK SOMEDAY, MOE.

09:19.040 --> 09:20.680
I DON'T KNOW.
HE'S TOUGH TO CATCH.

09:20.740 --> 09:22.580
HE KEEPS
CHANGING HIS NAME.

09:22.640 --> 09:24.910
MOE, I THINK
I'LL HAVE ANOTHER...

09:24.980 --> 09:26.050
WHOOPS.

09:26.110 --> 09:28.320
I'M A LITTLE LOW ON FUNDS.

09:28.380 --> 09:30.380
DO YOU THINK YOU COULD
COVER ME JUST THIS ONCE?

09:30.450 --> 09:31.390
NO. SORRY.

09:31.450 --> 09:32.790
WHY NOT?

09:32.850 --> 09:35.690
I THINK AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,
I DESERVE AN EXPLANATION.

09:35.750 --> 09:37.920
I DON'T THINK
YOU'RE EVER GONNA
GET ANOTHER JOB

09:37.990 --> 09:39.230
AND BE ABLE
TO PAY ME BACK.

09:39.290 --> 09:40.090
OH.

09:40.160 --> 09:41.130
DON'T WORRY.

09:41.190 --> 09:42.620
WE'RE STILL FRIENDS.

09:42.690 --> 09:46.460
Jukebox:
♪ I fall to pieces... ♪

09:46.530 --> 09:49.940
( <i>mumbling )</i>

09:50.000 --> 09:52.310
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT, HOMER?

09:52.370 --> 09:53.310
I'M FINE.

09:53.370 --> 09:54.840
I'M JUST THINKING.

09:54.910 --> 09:57.350
WELL, I'VE BEEN THINKING, TOO.

09:57.410 --> 10:01.280
YOU KNOW, HOMER, YOU'VE
ALWAYS BEEN SUCH A GOOD PROVIDER

10:01.350 --> 10:03.220
BUT WHEN WE GOT MARRIED

10:03.280 --> 10:07.150
MR. BURGER PROMISED I COULD
COME BACK TO MY OLD JOB

10:07.220 --> 10:08.590
ANYTIME I WANTED.

10:08.650 --> 10:11.550
YOU THINK YOU CAN STILL
DO THAT KIND OF WORK?

10:11.620 --> 10:12.920
SURE.  YOU NEVER FORGET.

10:12.990 --> 10:15.100
IT'S JUST LIKE RIDING A BICYCLE.

10:15.160 --> 10:16.430
( <i>horn honking )</i>

10:16.500 --> 10:20.230
HEY, MAMA,
WHERE'S MY FRIES ALREADY?

10:20.300 --> 10:22.000
( <i>growling )</i>

10:25.200 --> 10:26.460
DAD, EAT SOMETHING.

10:26.540 --> 10:28.140
IT'S GOT MUSTARD ON IT.

10:31.710 --> 10:35.950
ALL HE DOES IS LIE THERE
LIKE AN UNEMPLOYED WHALE.

10:36.010 --> 10:38.440
I DON'T WHAT ELSE TO DO.

10:40.390 --> 10:42.990
THERE'S ONLY ONE THING
WE CAN DO--

10:43.050 --> 10:45.280
TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF THE OLD GUY.

10:45.360 --> 10:48.160
YOU GOT TO SIGN
MY REPORT CARD, DAD.

10:51.200 --> 10:56.040
TV Announcer #1
Loaftime-- the cable network
for the unemployed

10:56.100 --> 10:59.510
will be back with more tips
on how to win the lottery
right after this.

10:59.570 --> 11:01.480
Announcer #2:
Unemployed?

11:01.540 --> 11:02.440
Out of work?

11:02.510 --> 11:03.610
Sober?

11:03.680 --> 11:05.280
You sat around the house
all day.

11:05.340 --> 11:06.770
But now it's Duff time.

11:06.850 --> 11:10.020
Duff-- the beer
that makes the days

11:10.080 --> 11:11.420
fly by.

11:11.480 --> 11:14.650
♪ I can't get enough
of that wonderful Duff ♪

11:14.720 --> 11:15.760
♪ Duff beer. ♪
BEER.

11:15.820 --> 11:18.030
NOW THERE'S
A TEMPORARY SOLUTION.

11:19.930 --> 11:22.630
THERE MUST BE SOME BEER
HERE SOMEWHERE.

11:22.690 --> 11:23.650
AH...

11:23.730 --> 11:24.500
MAYBE IN HERE.

11:26.870 --> 11:28.170
DAMN!

11:28.230 --> 11:29.730
I NEED MONEY!

11:43.850 --> 11:44.820
OH, NO.

11:44.880 --> 11:47.110
WHAT HAVE I DONE?

11:47.190 --> 11:51.260
I SMASHED OPEN MY LITTLE BOY'S
PIGGY BANK, AND FOR WHAT?

11:51.320 --> 11:53.250
A FEW MEASLY CENTS.

11:53.330 --> 11:55.930
NOT EVEN ENOUGH TO BUY ONE BEER.

11:55.990 --> 11:57.250
WAIT A MINUTE.

11:57.330 --> 11:59.600
LET ME COUNT AND MAKE SURE.

11:59.660 --> 12:00.890
NOT EVEN CLOSE.

12:04.070 --> 12:08.640
<i>DEAR FAMILY,
I AM AN UTTER FAILURE</i>

12:08.710 --> 12:11.810
<i>AND YOU'LL BE BETTER OFF
WITHOUT ME.</i>

12:11.880 --> 12:16.750
<i>BY THE TIME YOU READ THIS,
I WILL BE IN MY WATERY GRAVE.</i>

12:16.820 --> 12:21.160
<i>I CAN ONLY LEAVE YOU WITH
THE WORDS MY FATHER GAVE ME:</i>

12:21.220 --> 12:25.260
<i>STAND TALL, HAVE COURAGE
AND NEVER GIVE UP.</i>

12:25.320 --> 12:29.590
<i>I ONLY HOPE I CAN PROVIDE
A BETTER MODEL IN DEATH</i>

12:29.660 --> 12:31.600
<i>THAN I DID IN LIFE.</i>

12:31.660 --> 12:34.460
<i>WARMEST REGARDS...</i>

12:34.530 --> 12:39.930
<i>LOVE, HOMER J. SIMPSON.</i>

12:47.980 --> 12:49.450
( <i>squeaking )</i>

12:53.590 --> 12:55.820
( <i>grunting )</i>

13:03.960 --> 13:06.970
( <i>grunting )</i>

13:10.000 --> 13:11.770
NOTHING'S EASY.

13:18.690 --> 13:22.260
OH, LOOKS LIKE YOUNG SIMPSON
IS GOING TO KILL HIMSELF.

13:22.330 --> 13:23.500
MAYBE NOT.

13:23.570 --> 13:26.770
MAYBE HE'S JUST TAKING
HIS BOULDER FOR A WALK.

13:26.840 --> 13:29.070
( <i>laughing )</i>

13:29.140 --> 13:30.610
MOM, MOM, WAKE UP.

13:30.670 --> 13:31.810
WE'VE BEEN ROBBED!

13:31.870 --> 13:32.870
WHAT?

13:32.940 --> 13:34.010
SOMEONE SWIPED
MY PIGGY BANK.

13:35.410 --> 13:37.720
YOUR FATHER'S GONE, TOO.

13:37.780 --> 13:39.480
LOOK WHAT I FOUND!

13:43.420 --> 13:45.220
ALMOST THERE.

13:47.520 --> 13:48.560
( <i>honking )</i>

13:48.620 --> 13:49.780
HEY, YOU IDIOT!

13:49.860 --> 13:51.360
WATCH WHERE YOU'RE GOING.

13:55.030 --> 13:57.070
WELL, LIVE AND LEARN.

13:57.130 --> 13:58.400
THERE HE IS!

13:58.470 --> 14:00.240
DON'T DO IT, DAD.

14:08.780 --> 14:11.520
BOY, THIS INTERSECTION
IS DANGEROUS.

14:11.580 --> 14:14.180
SOMEONE OUGHT TO PUT
A STOP SIGN HERE.

14:15.750 --> 14:19.420
OH, HOMER, HOW COULD YOU
THINK OF KILLING YOURSELF?

14:19.490 --> 14:20.590
WE LOVE YOU.

14:20.660 --> 14:22.660
YEAH, DAD, WE LOVE YOU.

14:22.720 --> 14:24.290
YEAH.

14:24.360 --> 14:27.730
KILL MYSELF? KILLING MYSELF
IS THE LAST THING I'D EVER DO.

14:27.800 --> 14:29.530
NOW I HAVE A PURPOSE.

14:29.600 --> 14:30.900
A REASON TO LIVE.

14:30.970 --> 14:33.640
I DON'T CARE
WHO I HAVE TO FACE.

14:33.700 --> 14:36.340
I DON'T CARE
WHO I HAVE TO FIGHT.

14:36.400 --> 14:37.830
I WILL NOT REST

14:37.910 --> 14:40.380
UNTIL THIS STREET
GETS A STOP SIGN!

14:42.940 --> 14:46.370
NEXT ON THE AGENDA,
POLICE CHIEF WIGGUM
WILL GIVE US AN UPDATE

14:46.450 --> 14:48.250
ON OUR GRAFFITI PROBLEM.

14:48.320 --> 14:50.890
WELL, IT'S NO SECRET.
OUR CITY'S UNDER SIEGE

14:50.950 --> 14:53.080
BY A GRAFFITI VANDAL
KNOWN AS EL BARTO.

14:53.150 --> 14:57.380
POLICE ARTISTS HAVE A COMPOSITE
SKETCH OF THE CULPRIT.

14:57.460 --> 15:01.830
IF ANYONE HAS ANY INFORMATION,
PLEASE CONTACT US IMMEDIATELY.

15:01.900 --> 15:04.970
COOL, MAN.

15:05.030 --> 15:07.830
WOULDN'T WANT TO RUN INTO HIM
IN A DARK ALLEY.

15:07.900 --> 15:09.560
AND NOW, NEW BUSINESS.

15:09.640 --> 15:11.810
HOMER SIMPSON, LOCAL RESIDENT,
HAS SOMETHING.

15:11.870 --> 15:12.900
MR. SIMPSON.

15:12.970 --> 15:14.340
DON'T BE NERVOUS.

15:14.410 --> 15:15.950
WE BELIEVE IN YOU, HOMER.

15:17.380 --> 15:18.580
AHEM.

15:18.650 --> 15:21.620
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
ESTEEMED COUNCILMEN

15:21.680 --> 15:23.080
BOYS AND GIRLS

15:23.150 --> 15:26.090
RETIRED PEOPLE
WITH NOTHING BETTER TO DO--

15:26.150 --> 15:28.350
DANGER COMES IN
MANY, MANY FORMS

15:28.420 --> 15:29.750
FROM THE DINOSAURS

15:29.820 --> 15:32.890
THAT TORMENTED
OUR CAVEMAN ANCESTORS TO...

15:32.960 --> 15:34.970
SIMPSON, GET
TO THE POINT.

15:35.030 --> 15:38.240
WE SHOULD PUT A STOP SIGN
AT D STREET AND 12th.

15:38.300 --> 15:39.470
ALL IN FAVOR?

15:39.530 --> 15:40.560
AYE.
AYE.

15:40.640 --> 15:41.940
APPROVED.
MEETING ADJOURNED.

15:42.000 --> 15:43.060
COFFEE AND MAPLE LOGS
IN THE LOBBY.

15:43.140 --> 15:44.710
WOW!

15:44.770 --> 15:46.670
THEY LISTENED TO ME.

15:46.740 --> 15:48.010
ALL RIGHT, DAD!

15:48.080 --> 15:49.280
WAY TO GO, HOMER!

15:49.340 --> 15:50.970
YOU DID IT, HOMER.

15:51.050 --> 15:53.220
IF THEY THINK I'M GONNA
STOP WITH THAT STOP SIGN,

15:53.280 --> 15:54.550
THEY'RE SADLY MISTAKEN.

16:18.540 --> 16:21.150
OH, HOMER, I AM
SO PROUD OF YOU!

16:21.210 --> 16:22.910
PROUD? PROUD OF WHAT?

16:22.980 --> 16:23.980
WELL, EVERYTHING.

16:24.050 --> 16:26.020
YOUR DIP SIGN, FOR INSTANCE.

16:26.080 --> 16:28.390
NOW PEOPLE WON'T BE
CAUGHT OFF GUARD

16:28.450 --> 16:30.490
BY THAT LITTLE <i>MMM IN THE ROAD.</i>

16:30.550 --> 16:32.020
WHAT A GREAT FAMILY.

16:32.090 --> 16:34.390
BUT COME ON, WE ALL KNOW
THIS IS SMALL POTATOES.

16:34.460 --> 16:36.830
THERE'S A DANGER IN THIS TOWN

16:36.890 --> 16:40.060
THAT IS BIGGER THAN
ALL THE DIPS PUT TOGETHER.

16:40.130 --> 16:41.030
WHAT, DAD?

16:41.100 --> 16:43.030
I'M TALKING ABOUT THAT!

16:45.130 --> 16:47.690
YOU DON'T MEAN
YOU'RE GOING TO TAKE ON
YOUR OLD BOSSES?

16:47.770 --> 16:48.870
WOW!

16:48.940 --> 16:50.640
GEE, DAD'S A HERO.

16:50.710 --> 16:51.680
WHAT'D YOU SAY, SON?

16:51.740 --> 16:52.880
NOTHING.

16:52.940 --> 16:54.480
THAT'S OKAY.

16:54.540 --> 16:57.600
I'LL JUST ASSUME YOU SAID
WHAT I THOUGHT I HEARD YOU SAY.

17:00.010 --> 17:02.940
Man:
He also brought you
the speed bumps...

17:03.020 --> 17:04.390
( <i>cheering )</i>

17:04.450 --> 17:06.480
the dip signs...

17:06.550 --> 17:10.720
THE 15-MILE-PER-HOUR
SPEED LIMIT ON MAIN STREET.

17:10.790 --> 17:12.030
( <i>booing )</i>

17:12.089 --> 17:13.690
I GIVE YOU THE MAN

17:13.760 --> 17:16.770
WHOSE VERY NAME IS SYNONYMOUS
WITH SAFETY:

17:16.829 --> 17:18.800
HOMER SIMPSON!

17:18.869 --> 17:21.000
( <i>crowd chanting: )
<i>HOMER! HOMER!</i></i>

17:21.069 --> 17:22.369
THANK YOU.

17:22.440 --> 17:25.810
UNLIKE MOST OF YOU,
I AM NOT A NUT--

17:25.869 --> 17:28.200
JUST A GOOD, HONEST AMERICAN

17:28.280 --> 17:32.620
WHO OPPOSES WRONGDOING
AND ESPECIALLY CARELESSNESS

17:32.680 --> 17:34.520
WHEREVER THEY OCCUR.

17:34.580 --> 17:35.940
HMM...

17:36.020 --> 17:37.720
LOOK AT THAT MAN.

17:37.790 --> 17:40.820
HE HAS THE CROWD
IN THE PALM OF HIS HAND.

17:40.890 --> 17:43.990
HAVEN'T SEEN ANYTHING LIKE IT
SINCE JOLSON.

17:44.060 --> 17:45.460
WHO IS HE?

17:45.530 --> 17:47.730
THAT'S HOMER SIMPSON, SIR.

17:47.800 --> 17:50.070
HE USED TO WORK HERE
IN THE PLANT

17:50.130 --> 17:52.340
BUT WE FIRED HIM
FOR GROSS INCOMPETENCE.

17:52.400 --> 17:54.740
OH, SO THAT'S HIS LITTLE GAME.

17:54.800 --> 17:57.160
GET THIS SIMPSON CHARACTER
UP HERE RIGHT NOW.

17:57.240 --> 17:58.410
BUT, MR. BURNS...

17:58.470 --> 18:00.200
I SAID DO IT.

18:00.270 --> 18:02.600
NOW DO IT, DO IT, DO IT!

18:02.680 --> 18:08.120
OUR LIVES ARE AT THE HANDS OF
MEN NO SMARTER THAN YOU OR I...

18:08.180 --> 18:11.080
MANY OF THEM INCOMPETENT BOOBS.

18:11.150 --> 18:14.310
I KNOW THIS BECAUSE
I'VE WORKED ALONGSIDE THEM

18:14.390 --> 18:15.960
GONE BOWLING WITH THEM

18:16.020 --> 18:20.090
WATCHED THEM PASS ME OVER
FOR PROMOTIONS TIME AND AGAIN

18:20.160 --> 18:22.030
AND I SAY THIS STINKS.

18:22.100 --> 18:23.300
( <i>crowd cheering )</i>

18:23.360 --> 18:24.760
RIGHT ON, DAD!

18:24.830 --> 18:28.860
HEY, SIMPSON, BURNS WANTS
TO TALK TO YOU PRIVATELY.

18:28.940 --> 18:30.040
PRIVATELY?

18:30.100 --> 18:31.330
YES.

18:31.410 --> 18:32.380
STAY HERE.

18:32.440 --> 18:34.040
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

18:34.110 --> 18:36.480
( <i>cheering )</i>

18:38.750 --> 18:40.920
AH, HOMER SIMPSON.

18:40.980 --> 18:43.620
AT LAST, WE MEET.

18:43.690 --> 18:45.160
SAME HERE.

18:45.220 --> 18:49.830
SIMPSON, I WANT YOU TO REJOIN
OUR POWER PLANT FAMILY.

18:49.890 --> 18:51.360
SORRY, NO CAN DO.

18:51.430 --> 18:53.030
HEAR ME OUT, SIMPSON.

18:53.090 --> 18:56.620
I DON'T WANT YOU TO COME
BACK AS A TECHNICAL SUPERVISOR

18:56.700 --> 18:58.340
OR SUPERVISING TECHNICIAN

18:58.400 --> 19:01.040
OR WHATEVER THE HELL
YOU USED TO DO.

19:01.100 --> 19:05.280
I WANT YOU TO BE IN CHARGE
OF SAFETY HERE AT THE PLANT.

19:05.340 --> 19:06.510
SAFETY?

19:06.570 --> 19:08.700
BUT, SIR,
IF TRUTH BE KNOWN

19:08.780 --> 19:11.980
I ACTUALLY CAUSED MORE
ACCIDENTS AROUND HERE THAN
ANY OTHER EMPLOYEE.

19:12.050 --> 19:14.820
EVEN A FEW DOOZIES
NO ONE EVER FOUND OUT ABOUT.

19:14.880 --> 19:17.740
THE GENEROUS OFFER I'M MAKING
IS GOOD FOR EXACTLY...

19:17.820 --> 19:20.460
30 SECONDS, SIMPSON.

19:20.520 --> 19:22.560
<i>ME IN CHARGE OF SAFETY?</i>

19:22.620 --> 19:25.150
<i>THIS PLACE COULD BLOW SKY HIGH.</i>

19:25.230 --> 19:27.500
<i>I'LL CONCENTRATE
ON MY WORK NOW.</i>

19:27.560 --> 19:30.030
<i>HEY, THIS GUY'S DESK
SURE IS BIG.</i>

19:30.100 --> 19:32.270
<i>I CAN'T LET MARGE
SUPPORT THE FAMILY.</i>

19:32.330 --> 19:35.600
<i>THIS GUY'S GOT THE CLEANEST
SHIRT I'VE EVER SEEN.</i>

19:35.670 --> 19:36.570
<i>WHAT SHOULD I..?</i>

19:36.640 --> 19:37.570
SIMPSON, TIME'S UP.

19:37.640 --> 19:40.010
WHAT THE HEY?
I'LL TAKE THE JOB.

19:40.070 --> 19:41.030
EXCELLENT.

19:41.110 --> 19:43.010
YOUR FIRST DUTY WILL BE

19:43.080 --> 19:45.750
TO STEP OUT ON THE BALCONY

19:45.810 --> 19:49.110
AND TELL THAT CROWD
THIS PLANT IS SAFE.

19:49.180 --> 19:50.610
WHAT?!

19:50.690 --> 19:52.260
GO ON, HOMER.

19:52.320 --> 19:57.130
( <i>crowd chanting: )
<i>HOMER! HOMER!</i></i>

19:57.190 --> 19:58.730
Marge:
YAY, HOMER!

19:58.790 --> 20:00.490
Lisa:
GO, DAD!

20:00.560 --> 20:03.100
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
THIS PLANT IS...

20:11.070 --> 20:12.340
OH!

20:12.410 --> 20:13.640
SIT TIGHT.

20:13.710 --> 20:15.010
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

20:15.080 --> 20:16.050
( <i>cheering )</i>

20:18.480 --> 20:21.250
I CAN'T DO IT,
MR. BURNS.

20:21.320 --> 20:24.720
YOU MEAN, YOU'RE WILLING
TO GIVE UP A GOOD JOB
AND A RAISE

20:24.790 --> 20:26.620
JUST FOR YOUR PRINCIPLES?

20:26.690 --> 20:28.930
WHEN YOU PUT IT THAT WAY

20:28.990 --> 20:31.500
IT DOES SOUND
A LITTLE FARFETCHED.

20:31.560 --> 20:33.760
BUT THAT'S THE LUG
YOU'RE LOOKING AT.

20:33.830 --> 20:37.370
AND I VOW TO CONTINUE SPENDING
EVERY FREE MINUTE I HAVE

20:37.430 --> 20:39.040
CRUSADING FOR SAFETY.

20:39.100 --> 20:41.370
OF COURSE, I'D HAVE A LOT LESS
OF THOSE FREE MINUTES

20:41.440 --> 20:43.210
IF YOU GAVE ME THE JOB.

20:43.270 --> 20:46.280
YOU'RE NOT AS STUPID
AS YOU LOOK OR SOUND

20:46.340 --> 20:48.710
OR OUR BEST TESTING INDICATES.

20:48.780 --> 20:50.350
YOU'VE GOT THE JOB.

20:50.410 --> 20:51.980
NOW GET TO WORK!

20:52.050 --> 20:53.680
I'LL GET TO WORK

20:53.750 --> 20:57.220
BUT FIRST, I HAVE TO SAY
GOOD-BYE TO SOME FRIENDS.

20:58.450 --> 21:00.380
( <i>cheering )</i>

21:00.450 --> 21:03.050
FRIENDS, YOU HAVE COME
TO DEPEND ON ME

21:03.120 --> 21:05.520
AS YOUR SAFETY WATCHDOG

21:05.590 --> 21:07.190
SO YOU WON'T SCRAPE YOURSELF

21:07.260 --> 21:10.000
OR STUB YOUR TOES
OR BLOW YOURSELVES UP.

21:10.060 --> 21:11.690
BUT YOU CAN'T DEPEND ON ME

21:11.770 --> 21:13.740
ALL YOUR LIFE.

21:13.800 --> 21:15.570
YOU HAVE TO LEARN

21:15.640 --> 21:18.840
THAT THERE'S A LITTLE
HOMER SIMPSON IN ALL OF US.

21:18.910 --> 21:21.980
AND I'M GOING TO HAVE TO LIVE
WITHOUT YOUR RESPECT AND AWE.

21:22.040 --> 21:25.340
THE ONLY REASON
I'M TELLING YOU THIS

21:25.410 --> 21:28.880
IS I'M GOING TO BE LEAVING YOU.

21:28.950 --> 21:30.290
( <i>gasping )</i>

21:30.350 --> 21:31.860
BUT DON'T WORRY.

21:31.920 --> 21:35.360
I HAVE JUST BEEN APPOINTED
THE NEW SAFETY INSPECTOR

21:35.420 --> 21:37.250
AT THIS VERY PLANT.

21:37.330 --> 21:40.900
AND A BIG, FAT RAISE!

21:43.630 --> 21:44.700
THAT'S MY POP
UP THERE!

21:44.770 --> 21:45.670
DAD, WATCH OUT!

21:49.000 --> 21:50.400
WHOA, EASY.
DON'T DROP ME.
BE CAREFUL.

21:50.470 --> 21:51.710
<i>HOMER! HOMER!</i>

21:55.010 --> 21:58.220
Captioned by
The Caption Center
WGBH Educational Foundation

22:59.470 --> 23:01.330
SHH!
